               CM Creator Installation

Program installation consists of two steps:

1. Install Java, if necessary
2. Install CM Creator


Java Installation
-----------------

1. Check if a Java Development Kit (JDK) or Java Runtime Environment
   (JRE) is installed on your system by opening a command line window,
   then typing the command:
     java -version

   The response should be similar to
     > java -version
     java version "1.8.0_152"
     Java(TM) SE Runtime Environment (build 1.8.0_152-b16)
     Java HotSpot(TM) Client VM (build 25.152-b16, mixed mode)

2. If the response is something like "command not found", then download 
   a JRE or JDK version 8 or later from

     http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html

   and install per the instructions.

3. Repeat step 1 to be sure it is installed correctly.



CM Creator Installation for Windows
-----------------------------------

1 Download the distribution file
     jreality_v0.5-win.zip

2 Unzip the distribution file by double-clicking it.

  This creates two additional files, one of which is
     install_creator_v0.5-win.bat

2 Execute the file
     install_creator_v0.5-win.bat
  by double-clicking it.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

               CM Creator Execution and Usage

CM Creator Execution
--------------------

In the C:\jreality\v0.5 directory, execute the file
     creator_v0.5.bat


CM Creator Usage
----------------
Upon initiation, the program displays a pop-up menu for selecting the
level of user help desired. New users should select "A Beginner." In
Beginner mode, hovering the mouse over a program control (menu item, 
button, text field, etc) displays a help window containing documentation 
for that control.

New users may wish to move the help window nearer to the center of
the screen, and resize it larger. The help window documentation can
then be used to learn the purpose and operation of each program
control as the program is used by hovering the mouse over the control.

New users are encouraged to read the help documentation for the "Intro
Docs" entry at the top of the "Creator" menu, as well as documentation
for all of the "Intro Docs" submenu items. The organization and parts
of the CM Creator main window are documented in the help page for the
"Creator" menubar entry.

Several sample Compartmentalized Models are supplied with the program,
the most extensive of which is a CModel of the USS Texas (BB 35). These
sample CModels are accessed via the "Select Existing" menu item in the
"CModel" menu.

